Package: LINDA
Type: Package
Title: An ILP Formulation to Integrate Alternative Splicing with Protein Network Analysis
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Enio",
           family = "Gjerga",
           role = c("cre", "aut"),
           email = "enio.gjerga@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8042-0395"))
           )
Description: A method that combines estimated transcription factor activities with alternative splicing analysis and prior knowledge of protein-protein and domain-domain interactions in order to infer upstream protein regulatory networks. Alternative-splicing evidence can be integrated either as hard ILP constraints that exclude significantly affected reactions or as soft objective-function penalties that discourage affected reactions while keeping them feasible.
